<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>☃️ M003 Extension — Build the Snow Golem (Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Snow Golem (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate (Extension, after Week 6) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 40 minutes</p>
<p>Build a <strong>standing snow golem</strong> in 3D — a snow body, a carved-pumpkin head, coal buttons down the front, and two stick arms. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>: x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>deeper</strong> (forward).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move your feet, move your golem.</p>
<p>🎨 Snow = <strong>snow block</strong>. Head = <strong>carved pumpkin</strong>. Buttons + eyes = <strong>coal block</strong>. Arms = a <strong>brown block</strong> (oak log).</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set. Write a sentence about what you will see.</p>
<pre><code>place snow block at (3, 1, 1)
place snow block at (3, 2, 1)
place snow block at (3, 3, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. Does this snow tower go across, up, or deeper? Which number changes?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place snow block at (3, 3, 1)
place snow block at (3, 3, 2)
place snow block at (3, 3, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. Does it go across, up, or deeper? Which number changes?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place snow block at (3, 4, 1)
place coal block at (3, 4, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Same (x, y, z). Do you see snow, coal, or both? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each code block is broken. Read what it should do, fix it, then explain why the original was wrong and your fix works.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — A coal button belongs <strong>on the front</strong> of the body at (3, 4, 1). The code has only <strong>two</strong> numbers, so it lands flat on the ground.</p>
<pre><code>place coal block at (3, 4)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — An eye should sit <strong>up high on the front</strong> of the head at (4, 7, 1). The last two numbers are <strong>swapped</strong>, so it lands in the wrong place.</p>
<pre><code>place coal block at (4, 1, 7)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Walk around the ☃️ snow golem in the world. Then build a snow golem on your home spot.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Snow body:</strong> fill snow blocks from (2, 1, 1) to (4, 5, 1) — a tall tower.</p>
<p><strong>Pumpkin head on top</strong> (bigger y): fill carved pumpkin from (2, 6, 1) to (4, 7, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Two coal eyes on the head</strong> (front): coal block at (2, 7, 1) and (4, 7, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Two coal buttons on the body</strong> (front): coal block at (3, 4, 1) and (3, 2, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Two arms out the sides:</strong> a brown block at (1, 4, 1) and (5, 4, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Add depth:</strong> build the snow body and pumpkin head again at z = 2. The eyes, buttons, and arms stay on the <strong>front only</strong> (z = 1).</p>
<p>💡 Tip: the head goes <strong>up</strong> (bigger y). The arms poke <strong>out</strong> (x = 1 and x = 5). A bigger z means <strong>deeper</strong> into the wall.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera at the golem. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
